main event: An unidentified object was sighted heading 130 degrees at an altitude of approximately 2000 feet with a yellow or amber light and jack-o'-lantern shape.
interesting points: Sighted object was reported to have no markings observed., The speed of the object was estimated at 1,000 knots., The observation was classified as insufficient data and possibly linked to the jet stream., The report originated from a military source and involved various military commands., The sighting occurred on 11 February 1956.
